  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I know if a shy guy likes me?",
  "response": "Figuring out if a shy guy likes you can be challenging because he might not express his feelings openly. Here are some signs that could indicate his interest:\n\n1. **Body Language**: Pay attention to his body language. If he often finds himself facing you, maintaining eye contact, or showing nervous habits like fidgeting, it could indicate interest.\n\n2. **Communication Initiation**: Even if he doesn\u2019t talk much, he might make small efforts to initiate conversation or find reasons to talk to you.\n\n3. **Active Listening**: Notice if he listens intently when you speak and remembers small details about your conversations.\n\n4. **Acts of Kindness**: He might go out of his way to help you or perform small acts of kindness as a way of expressing his interest.\n\n5. **Social Media Interaction**: He could be trying to engage with you through social media by liking your posts or leaving comments.\n\n6. **Presence**: A shy guy might try to be around you more often, even if he doesn\u2019t say much. He might attend events or places he knows you\u2019ll be.\n\n7. **Nervousness Around You**: If he seems more nervous or awkward when you\u2019re around, it might be a sign he likes you and is worried about making a good impression.\n\n8. **Friends\u2019 Behavior**: His friends might know about his feelings and could tease him when you are around, or they might treat you differently.\n\n9. **Compliments and Flattery**: He might give subtle compliments, either directly or indirectly, through friends.\n\n10. **Interest in Your Interests**: He may show an interest in your hobbies or preferences as a way to connect with you.\n\nRemember, it\u2019s important to be patient and give him time to become comfortable expressing his feelings. If you like him too, encouraging and reassuring him in subtle ways can also help.",
